# Data Dictionary — gebhart2023_math_framework

## Data source
American Physical Society bibliographic data (~630K papers) + Nobel laureate dataset (Li et al. 2019) — Physics citation network + Nobel-prize papers
Access: partial; Provenance: APS restricted; Nobel dataset public (Scientific Data)

## Key variables
- Unit of analysis: paper
- Time window: 1893-2019
- Sample N: 630000
- Filter rules: APS physics, Nobel laureate subset

## Indicator definitions
- Formula: Relates CD Index to betweenness centrality; B_k and Π_k disruption measures
- Parameters: centrality window
- Computation steps: build citation graph, compute betweenness, relate to CD
